License posture

All rights reserved. The author is evaluating license terms and has
not yet granted public permissions to use, modify, or redistribute
this work outside of viewing the source on GitHub.

Expected outcome: this notice will be replaced with a real
open-source license (likely MIT, Apache-2.0, or AGPL-3.0) once the
project's direction is clearer. Until then, please contact
jasoncarreira on GitHub for use inquiries.

What you may do today:
- View the source publicly on GitHub.
- Fork on GitHub for personal inspection (per GitHub's Terms of
  Service, which grant a limited fork-and-review right separate
  from the underlying license).
- Reference the design ideas, file pointers, or mechanisms in your
  own work — copyright protects the expression, not the underlying
  ideas.

What you may not do today:
- Use the code in production.
- Modify and redistribute it.
- Build a derivative work and publish it.

If any of those are blocking you, opening an issue or reaching out
directly is the fastest path to a permission grant.
